<P>
   LAMA-RIVALS (Rumtek, India) _ Deshin Shekpa was born during the
year of the male wood mouse (1384), and it is said he could be
heard chanting a mantra and reciting the alphabet while still
inside his mother's womb. At the moment of his birth, he boldly
proclaimed himself to be the fifth incarnation of the Karmapa, one
of Tibetan Buddhism's holiest figures. Now, two rival incarnations
have strained relations between India and China, and one lama says:
``Buddha would not be laughing right now. This is all about
politics. It's a story filled with many traitors and betrayals.''
By Barry Bearak.
