<P>
   CRUISE-PORTS _ Major cruise lines are trying the bring the ocean
to Atlanta. Or at least make it easier for us and other Southerners
to get on their ships. Time was, if you wanted to take a cruise to
the Caribbean or other warm-weather vacation destinations south of
the United States, you had to depart from Miami or Fort Lauderdale.
But, thanks to booming business in recent years, major lines have
expanded their Southeastern ports, to Port Canaveral farther up
Florida's Atlantic coast, as well as Tampa, New Orleans and _ local
travelers, listen up _ Charleston. (Hamilton, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)WITH PHOTOS.
