<P>
   BOOKS-CAFE _ AUSTIN, Texas _ Ricardo checks out the culture of
bookstores. People go there not only to buy books. (sometimes they
don't buy at all). Looking for an angle of a sense of community and
looking for book stores that have regulars. (Gandara, Austin
American-Statesman)
</P>
<P>
   BOOK-KIDS _ Roundup of the latest children's books. (Bookman,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   BOOKS-ANDREAYOUNG _ Andrea Young, daughter of Andy and Jean
Young, describes the legacy her late mother left in ``Life Lessons
My Mother Taught Me.'' From the simple _ ``Always Wear Lipstick'' _
to the serious _ ``Resistance Is a Way of Life'' _ Young recounts
anecdotes of her mother's activism and their family life in the
spotlight. Q&AMP;A. (O'Briant, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) MOVED
MONDAY.
</P>
<P>
   BOOKS-NIGHT _ A review of ``Love With the Night: The American
Romance'' with Robert Kennedy, by Ronald Steel. (Blackburn, Palm
Beach Post). 20. MOVED MONDAY.
</P>
