<P>
   GARCIA-COLUMN _ AUSTIN, Texas _ When you get right down to it,
Texas judicial races are a lot like a back-room craps game. In
both, a wrong move can have dangerous consequences, and people
trust an awful lot to luck. (Arnold Garcia is editorial page editor
of the Austin American-Statesman) MOVED
</P>
<P>
   YOUNG-COLUMN _ WACO, Texas _ New Hampshire's Republican lesson
proves most elemental: Donors help. But to win, you need voters.
Tuesday's result also raises questions about the soul of the
Republican Party, or at least those who claim it. (John Young is
opinion page editor of the Waco Tribune-Herald) MOVED
</P>
<P>
   NETHAWAY-COLUMN _ WACO, Texas _ Back when I was protesting the
segregation of my native South, I used to wonder what I would have
done at the same age during the Civil War. (Rowland Nethaway is
senior editor of the Waco Tribune-Herald) MOVED.
</P>
