<P>
   LIFESTYLE
</P>
<P>
   DINOSAURS-EXHIBIT _ ATLANTA _ Dinosaur experts say the ambitious
new dinosaur exhibit at Fernbank Science Center in Atlanta is the
first of kind anywhere and will attract scientists from around the
country as eager as kids to see the Argentinosaurus and the
Giganotasaurus. The story will explain the significance of the
discovery of these dinosaurs and the exhibit. (Hendrick, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 35. WITH PHOTOS.
</P>
<P>
   EDs: Moving in (a) General News and (l) Lifestyle categories.
</P>
<P>
   CRUISING-SOCIAL _ The social aspects of cruising. So you've met
your dinner-mates for the next 5 days. What if you don't like them?
(Moffett, Palm Beach Post). 28. WITH PHOTO. MOVED MONDAY.
</P>
<P>
   TRAVEL
</P>
<P>
   CRUISE-PORTS _ Major cruise lines are trying the bring the ocean
to Atlanta. Or at least make it easier for us and other Southerners
to get on their ships. Time was, if you wanted to take a cruise to
the Caribbean or other warm-weather vacation destinations south of
the United States, you had to depart from Miami or Fort Lauderdale.
But, thanks to booming business in recent years, major lines have
expanded their Southeastern ports, to Port Canaveral farther up
Florida's Atlantic coast, as well as Tampa, New Orleans and _ local
travelers, listen up _ Charleston. (Hamilton, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)WITH PHOTOS.
</P>
<P>
   Eds: Embargoed for Sunday, Feb. 6.
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   ITINERARIES _ Cruise itineararies for ships sailing out of
Charleston, Tampa and New Orleans. (Hamilton, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). WITH PHOTOS.
</P>
<P>
   Eds: Embargoed for Sunday, Feb. 6.
</P>
<P>
   YANGTZERIVER-CRUISE _ YANGTZE RIVER, China _ A three-day Yangtze
River cruise was the highlight of our 17-day trip to China, a
fascinating study into the contrast between ancient and modern,
natural and man-made, beautiful and destructive. It was a trip
through places that will soon no longer exist. Once the massive
Three Gorges Dam is complete in 2009, the river will rise 50 meters
(approximately 150 feet), enveloping much of the life we saw along
its banks.(Wexler, Atlanta Journal-Constitution freelancer; not for
use by NYTNS clients). WITH PHOTOS.
</P>
<P>
   Eds: Embargoed for Sunday, Feb. 6.
</P>
<P>
   GETAWAY _ With Valentine's Day coming up, singer-actress Claudia
Church, wife of Nashville singer-songwriter Rodney Crowell,
suggests romantic places to stay, see, shop, dine in Music City.
(Thrasher, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   GETAWAY-FESTIVALS _ Southern happenings. (Thrasher, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) MOVED.
