<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-HEARST-FEATURE-BUDGET-HNS </SLUG>
  
<TEXT>
<P>
   &UR; Thursday, Feb. 3, 2000 &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; EDITORS: &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   The Hearst News Service will file these stories for Friday. If
you have questions, please call Tim Spence at 202-298-6920.
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; (``HNS'' appears in all sluglines.)
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   BORDER-SECURITY (Lake Placid, N.Y.) _ Security along the
Canadian border is being tightened as police and counterterrorism
SWAT teams move into Lake Placid for the inaugural Winter Goodwill
Games. FBI agents said there have been no terrorist threats
directly linked to the games. By BRENDAN LYONS.
</P>
<P>
   COPS-TRIAL (Albany, N.Y.) _ Local attorneys gave defense lawyers
in the Amadou Diallo case high marks for weaving together their
strategy in four strong opening statements to give jurors the same
message over and over again. By CAROL DeMARE.
</P>
<P>
   FEATURES/LIFESTYLE (``l'' category)
</P>
<P>
   SUV-SPEED(Troy, N.Y.) _ When it comes to cars, perception is
everything, and few autos on the road scream status like the sleek,
stark sport utility vehicle. But perceptions can lie. A new study
by Rensselaer Polytechnic Institute on the psychology of
transportation suggests that because SUV drivers sit higher from
the ground, they have the dangerous illusion of driving slower than
they really are. By ANDREW BROWNSTEIN.
</P>
<P>
   ENTERTAINMENT (``e'' category)
</P>
<P>
   FILM-LEIGH (Undated) _ Director Mike Leigh talks about the
critically acclaimed ``Topsy-Turvy,'' the new film about Gilbert &AMP;
Sullivan and the crisis in their creative partnership. By LOUIS B.
PARKS.
</P>
<P>
   KIDS-HALL (Toronto) _ A backstage look at the Kids In The Hall
reunion tour. The troupe's 25-city tour is called ``Kids in the
Hall 2000: Same Guys ... Different Dresses.'' By SHERRY THOMAS.
</P>
<P>
   VIDEO-REVIEW (Undated) _ A review of the video and DVD versions
of Disney's ``Tarzan,'' and other notes on ``The Maltese Falcon,''
a ``Jumanji'' collectors' edition, extra footage for ``The
Insider'' and a documentary on the real person in ``Boys Don't
Cry.'' By BRUCE WESTBROOK.
</P>
<P>
   MUSIC-GAY-DAD (Houston) _ Gay Dad, a British pop band that has
been dogged with rumors about its name, wishes the name thing would
just go away. The group has a hit single, ``To Earth With Love,''
and opens for the Pretenders in Houston. By MICHAEL D. CLARK.
</P>
<P>
   BUSINESS/FINANCIAL NEWS (``f'' category)
</P>
<P>
   MARKETING-COLUMN (Houston) _ After he turned 50, Joel Cohen knew
something had to give. Tired of not having fun in the advertising
world, he came up with a dream plan and launched
Americanadagencies.com, a listing of Web sites for agencies in 20
U.S. cities. He now works for a number of restaurants, a hockey
team in Toledo, Ohio, and gets regular speaking gigs. Better still,
he is having more fun than he used to. By GREG HASSELL.
</P>
<P>
   FOOD (`d'' category)
</P>
<P>
   NUT-MIXES (Undated) _ Forget those salted peanut and cereal
concoctions, the nut mixes of the new millennium use pungent herbs
and spices and leave out fillers like cereal and candy. They're
trendy and tasteful, showing up in gourmet catalogs and wine bars.
And, most importantly, they can be made at home leaving out
preservatives that may be found in commercial products. By RUTH
FANTASIA.
</P>
<P>
   COMMENTARY (``k'' category)
</P>
<P>
   MORSE-COLUMN (San Francisco) _ What is it about airplanes? They
scare the hell out of us, and even though we're often told they're
safer than cars, we never believe it. Flying is magic, something
humans did in dreams long before the Wright brothers. When the
magic fails, very bad things happen, very fast, to very many
people. By ROB MORSE.
</P>
<P>
   LYNCH-COLUMN (Albany, N.Y.) _ OK, Al Sharpton was saying, one of
the cops publicly apologized to the Diallo family. That's fine. But
more than an apology is required. So, what are we going to do _
open the Albany County Jail, let everybody express regrets and send
them home? By DAN LYNCH.
</P>
