   Neurons are reservoirs of electrical charge. When stimulated, a
neuron sends an electrical signal and then needs some time to
recover.
</P>
<P>
   During a resting phase _ which can last 10 seconds and longer _
other active nerve cells continue to fire.
</P>
<P>
   In most instances this neural tradeoff is seamless and your
