<P>
   McCAIN-CALIF (Sacramento, Calif.) _ Despite his commanding
victory over Texas Gov. George W. Bush in the New Hampshire
primary, Arizona Sen. John McCain is likely to find the California
campaign crush favoring Bush because he has the resources to spend
vast amounts of money on television advertising. Bush also has the
support of the Republican establishment in the state. By ROBERT
SALLADAY.
</P>
<P>
   BUSH-McCAIN (Undated) _ With a new poll showing John McCain now
leading George W. Bush in South Carolina, Bush brings out veterans'
groups and decorated soldiers to endorse him and criticize McCain's
Senate record on POW-MIA issues. McCain responds by challenging
Bush to a debate on military issues ``any time, any where,'' and,
with the confidence of a front-runner, criticizes Bush for being
negative. By R.G. RATCLIFFE and GREG McDONALD.
</P>
<P>
   GORE-BRADLEY (Undated) _ Vice President Al Gore and former New
Jersey Sen. Bill Bradley turn their attention to the West Coast in
the quest for the Democratic presidential nomination. By PATTY
REINERT.
</P>
<P>
   WASHINGTON NEWS (``w'' category)
</P>
<P>
   DRUGS-TV (Washington) _ Denying accusations that his office
pressured TV networks to change their scripts, a White House aide
says anti-drug officials will continue their controversial practice
of providing financial incentives to networks that include
anti-drug content in their programs. However, Alan Levitt, director
of the National Youth Anti-Drug Media Campaign, says his office
will no longer provide ``guidance'' to television writers. By MARK
HELM.
</P>
<P>
   PELOSI-PRESS (Washington) _ Rep. Nancy Pelosi, a featured
entertainer at the annual winter bash for Congress and the press,
is assigned to tell why she isn't running for president. ``I
haven't come to that conclusion yet,'' she jokes. By the Hearst
Newspapers. (Already filed.)
</P>
<P>
   SPORTS (``s'' category)
</P>
<P>
   BKN-ROCKETS (Houston) _ The Houston Rockets try to keep their
11-game winning streak going as they play the Philadelphia 76ers.
By JONATHAN FEIGEN
</P>
<P>
