<P>
   BRITAIN-WALMART _ SUTTON, England _ The simple, yet potent ethos
that changed America now is working its way through Britain - and
is poised to sweep the rest of Europe. Last June, Bentonville,
Ark.-based Wal-Mart purchased Asda, Britain's No. 3 grocery story
chain for $10.8 billion. The stage was set for a retail revolution.
(Roughton, Cox News Service). WITH PHOTO.
