<P>
   VODAFONE-MANNESMANN (Dusseldorf, Germany) _ Ending a bruising
three-month hostile takeover brawl, two of the world's biggest
companies in wireless communications agreed on Thursday to merge in
a record $178 billion deal. In a stunning victory that had once
been considered unthinkable, Vodafone AirTouch PLC of Britain
negotiated the acquisition of Mannesmann AG of Germany, in an
all-stock transaction that easily shattered the previous record for
a takeover deal, America Online's $165 billion purchase of Time
Warner announced less than three weeks ago. If consummated, the
takeover will vastly expand the geographic reach of Vodafone, which
already is the world's biggest wireless telephone company, giving
it dominance in the European market. The company has major holdings
in the United States, Asia and Africa. By Edmund L. Andrews and
Andrew Ross Sorkin.
</P>
