   With graphic.
</P>
<P>
   CREDIT-LOSSES (New York) _ Chaos swept through the U.S. bond
market Thursday as traders and investors tried to make sense of a
spectacular and damaging rise in the price of the 30-year Treasury
bond. Tripping over themselves to buy 30-year bonds, investors and
traders drove the price of the bond up an unheard-of 3 percent
early in the morning. The yield on the bond fell from its Wednesday
close of 6.28 percent to as low as 5.93 percent before settling at
6.13 percent at the end of the day. By Gretchen Morgenson.
</P>
