chairwoman and chief executive of Mattel Inc. after a botched
acquisition led to a string of disappointing quarters. The
resignation of Barad, effective Thursday, came after a meeting of
the board of the world's largest toymaker in New York and as Mattel
reported a loss of $18.4 million for the latest quarter. By
Constance L. Hays.
