A5671 &Cx1f; tdt-z
u p BC-SPOT-BUDGET-BOS &LR;      02-03 0491
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-SPOT-BUDGET-BOS </SLUG>
  
 For Release FRIDAY AMs, February 4, 2000  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Boston Globe plans to move the following stories for use by
NYTimes News Service clients.
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR; For questions about stories, contact  &UR; Frank Perrotta  &LR; at the
Boston Globe,  &UR; 617-929-2597. &LR;  For individual purchase of graphics
or photos please call  &UR; 888-346-9867  &LR; or  &UR; 888-603-1036 &LR; .
</P>
<P>
   All stories will bear the BOS designator.
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; INTERNATIONAL (i) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   IRELAND-ULSTER (London) _ With the Irish Republican Army balking
at disarming, the British will introduce legislation to suspend the
fledgling power-sharing government in Ulster and reimpose direct
rule from London rather than allow Protestant unionists to walk out
and collapse the Belfast assembly. By Kevin Cullen. 1000 words.
</P>
<P>
   RUSSIA-BABITSKY (Moscow) _ Russian military says it has traded
dissident journalist Andrei Babitsky to Chechens for three Russian
soldiers. By Brian Whitmore. 850 words.
</P>
<P>
