<SLUG> BC-BAUER-QUITS-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
BAUER IS SAID TO PLAN TO LEAVE RACE ON FRIDAY 
</HEADLINE>
  (sw) 
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON _ Gary Bauer will end his campaign for the Republican
presidential nomination on Friday at a news conference in
Washington, where he will not endorse any of the other Republican
candidates, a friend close to the campaign said on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
   The announcement comes after Bauer finished with only 1 percent
of the Republican primary vote in New Hampshire on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
   When asked about the announcement, a spokesman, Timothy S.
Goeglein, said only that Bauer returned to Washington on Wednesday
and wanted a few days to catch his breath before holding a news
conference.
</P>
<P>
   Best known for his advocacy of conservative religious values and
as the longtime president of the Family Research Council, Bauer is
also chairman of the Campaign for Working Families.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
