Barad, the woman who turned Barbie into a $1.7 billion business,
stepped down on Thursday as chairwoman and chief executive of
Mattel Inc. after a botched acquisition led to a string of
disappointing quarters. Barad's resignation, effective Thursday,
came after a meeting of the board of the world's largest toymaker
