Kellie Chouest after it was recovered by an unmanned vehicle from
the Navy's Deep Submergence Unit Unmanned Vehicle Detachment,
Wednesday. The recorder was recovered from a depth of 700 feet in
the Pacific off the coast of northern Los Angeles. The Alaska
Airlines MD-83 crashed Monday killing 88 people. (Spike Call, U.S.
Navy/The New York Times)
