photo, was involved Wednesday night in stopping a Russian tanker in
the Persian Gulf, off the coast of the United Arab Emirates. The
tanker was stopped because of suspicions the ship was transporting
Iraqi oil. The naval ship is part of an international patrol
enforcing U.N. sanctions against Iraq. Russia demanded Thursday the
tanker be released and said the ship was carrying legal Iranian
fuel oil. (Lance Kirk, U.S. Navy/The New York Times)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT1) ABOARD KELLIE CHOUEST -- Feb. 3, 2000 --
