<HEADLINE>
RAIN DELAYS PLAY AT PEBBLE BEACH 
</HEADLINE>
   (Shorted) 
 (rk) 
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   PEBBLE BEACH, Calif. _ It happened again at Pebble Beach.
Everybody was wet, and nobody was surprised.
</P>
<P>
   In a development that has become expected at this picturesque
but puddle-filled event, rain and high winds forced Thursday's
first-round play of the AT&AMP;T Pebble Beach National Pro-Am to be
suspended.
</P>
<P>
   The tournament will be extended through Monday, with first-round
play resuming Friday morning, second-round play scheduled for
Saturday, third-round play for Sunday and final-round action for
Monday.
</P>
</TEXT>
