   THE REPUBLICANS  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   HE GETS AROUND
</P>
<P>
   Gov. George W. Bush came to Delaware on Thursday afternoon and
said the trip showed the sweep of his campaign. ``I think if
somebody is running for president of the United States, they need
to run in all the states,'' Bush told supporters in Dover. It was a
none-too-subtle dig at Sen. John McCain, who is largely ignoring
Delaware's primary on Feb. 8, focusing on South Carolina's on Feb
19.
</P>
