   THE DEMOCRATS
</P>
<P>
   DEBATES DELAYED
</P>
<P>
   Vice President Al Gore has rejected former Sen. Bill Bradley's
suggestion to start weekly debates Sunday on the NBC News program
``Meet the Press.'' Douglas Hattaway, a Gore spokesman, said the
schedule should be negotiated. ``He can't unilaterally dictate a
schedule when we've had this challenge outstanding for a long
time,'' Hattaway said, referring to a Gore offer of twice-weekly
debates. But Eric Hauser, Bradley's spokesman, said, ``Given the
vice president's interest in debating, we find this surprising.'' &QL;
</P>
